{{Infobox University |name = Dr. Gaur Hari Singhania Institute of Management and Research |native_name = GHS-IMR | image = [[File:ghsimr_logo.png|120px]] | caption = GHS-IMR, Kanpur |established = 1995 |director = Dr. (Prof.) Rakesh Premi |campus = [[Kamla Nagar]] [[Kanpur]] |city = [[Kanpur]] |state = [[Uttar Pradesh]] |country = [[India]]{{flagicon|IND}} |website = {{URL|www.ghsimr.ac.in}} | chairman = Shri Yadupati Singhania }}
'''Dr. Gaur Hari Singhania Institute of Management and Research''' ('''GHS-IMR'''), Kanpur,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghsimr.ac.in | title=Dr. Gaur Hari Singhania Institute of Management and Research}}</ref> is a Management Institute of North India. It was established in 1995 by JK Organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jkcement.com | title=JK Organization}}</ref> GHS-IMR offers two-year full-time Post Graduate Diploma in Management which is approved by [[All India Council for Technical Education]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aicte-india.org|title=All India Council for Technical Education}}</ref> and recognized as equivalent to MBA by [[Association of Indian Universities]] (AIU)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aiu.ac.in/index.asp|title=Association of Indian Universities}}</ref>.
==History==
Dr. Gaur Hari Singhania Institute of Management and Research was established in 1995 by JK Organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jkcement.com/|title=JK Organization}}</ref> GHS-IMR<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghsimr.ac.in |title=GHS-IMR, Kanpur}}</ref> is one of the oldest management institutes in Kanpur. GHS-IMR is an AICTE approved management college and offers two-year full-time Post Graduate Diploma in Management (PGDM). GHS-IMR today is an alma mater to over 1900+ alumni, who are working across many industries.<ref name="GHS-IMR, Kanpur">{{cite web |url=https://www.ghsimr.ac.in/page/about-us |title=About GHS-IMR}}</ref>
==Awards and rankings== [[File:Building of Dr. Gaur Hari Singhania Institute of Management and Research.jpg|thumb|Building of Dr. Gaur Hari Singhania Institute of Management and Research]] *"Ranked 45th Best B-School of India by Business India" * “Outstanding Institute of North India Award 2017”<ref name="Quality Education gets awarded">{{cite news| author = Devendra Jaiswal| title = Quality Education gets awarded| quote = Two Awards to GHS-IMR| newspaper = Times of India| date = 31 March 2017| url = http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com| accessdate = 31 March 2017}}</ref> *"20th promising B-School of India by Competition Success Review" *"Rated AA+ by Career360 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://bschool.careers360.com/dr-gaur-hari-singhania-institute-management-and-research-kanpur|title=Rated AA+ by Career 360}}</ref> * “Education Leadership Award 2017” by BBC Knowledge.<ref name="Quality Education gets awarded"/> * Excellence in Education Award by Governor of Uttar Pradesh, His Excellency Shri Ram Naik ji, hosted by Times Group * Ranked 87th in India by MBA Universe & The Hindu Business Line<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mbauniverse.com/mba-ranking/2017|title=MBA College Ranking 2017}}</ref>
==Programme Offered== ===PGDM=== The Post Graduate Diploma in Management (PGDM) is two-year full-time programme. During the two years, the student receives academic inputs in two parts: the Compulsory course and the Elective course. Largely, the compulsory courses are to be studied in the first year and the elective courses are in the second year. The students can opt for dual specialization in the areas of Marketing, Finance, Human Resource Management, Operations, International Business and Information Technology as per their choice and career aspiration. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/education/PGDM-or-MBA-dilemma-continues/article14690285.ece|title=PGDM or MBA, dilemma continues}}</ref>
